After this satisfactory settlenient the Archbishop continued his Visitation, without let or hindrance, till its close. On the very next day (3 July) he received the Bishop in his chainber at Exminster, and on his request granted him Licence to resume the exercise of his Peculiar Jurisdiction throughout the Diocese, ‘⁶ non obstante dependencia Visitacionis sue Metropolitice.’' 2
